<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">Best Hot Wallet vs. Best Cold Wallet: Which One Do You Need?</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Deciding between a hot wallet and a cold wallet for crypto storage is mostly determined by overall accessibility and security needs. Hot wallets are used for short-term storage, while cold wallets offer long-term security.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">What is a Crypto Hot Wallet?</span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A crypto hot wallet is used to store, send and receive crypto, and this wallet stays connected to the network. Hot wallets can include mobile apps, extensions and desktop wallets.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Hot wallets tend to be very accessible and quick to set up while also being cost-free. Most digital asset service providers have the best free crypto wallet available with a very simple and user-friendly design, perfect for the crypto beginner. On the other hand, because they are hot wallets working on the internet, they are vulnerable to online attacks like phishing and malware.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Regardless of the dangers, hot wallets are oftentimes necessary for users of DeFi and active traders. Provided that hot wallets have been secured and protected with two-factor authentication and backups, they can be a very reliable option as a daily-use hot wallet.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">What is a Crypto Cold Wallet?</span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A crypto cold wallet saves your private keys offline, which makes cold wallets one of the best ways to store your digital assets. There are two different types of cold wallets: hardware wallets and offline paper wallets; that&#8217;s why they&#8217;re often referred to as the best cold storage crypto wallet solutions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cold wallets are immune to online attacks like hacking and phishing. Devices such as hardware wallets are widely regarded as the best crypto hardware wallet options for long-term investors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">While cold wallets are less convenient for daily use, they offer unmatched security. For investors prioritising ownership and safety, they are often considered the best self-custody crypto wallet choice.</span></p>
