<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Transfer Delays (The Profit Killer)</span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The nightmare of a crypto arbitrage trader is transferring an asset between various exchanges when a blockchain network is clogged. The price difference has disappeared by the time it gets there, and you have an unwanted asset, sometimes even a loss. </span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Wallet Maintenance</span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Exchanges frequently put wallets into maintenance mode when there is high volatility, the time when arbitrage gaps are greatest. When this happens, you cannot trade to make profits. You can check how frequent this issue is before picking a crypto exchange arbitrage platform.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Exchange Solvency</span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The more exchanges you keep capital in, the higher your Counterparty Risk. When one of the exchanges collapses (the &#8220;FTX Scenario&#8221;), then your arbitrage gains are worth nothing. This is why you should pick reliable platforms to trade arbitrage.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Liquidity Issued </span></h3>
